CI for $\mu_d$ (or $\delta$):  [*How was $t^*$ calculated?*]{style="color:darkorange"}




::: columns
::: {.column width="50%"}

\begin{align}
\bar{x}_d &\pm t^*\cdot\frac{s_d}{\sqrt{n}}\\
-19.542 &\pm 2.069\cdot\frac{16.806}{\sqrt{24}}\\
-19.542 &\pm 2.069\cdot 3.43\\
-19.542 &\pm 7.096\\
(-26.638&, -12.445)
\end{align}

:::
::: {.column width="50%"}
Conclusion:  
We are 95% that the (population) mean difference in cholesterol levels after a vegetarian diet is between -26.638 mg/dL and -12.445 mg/dL.

* [_Based on the CI, is there evidence the diet made a difference in cholesterol levels? Why or why not?_]{style="color:darkorange"}
